schen Werkes des in Berlin tätigen Römers Francesco Valentini. An seinem Beispiel wird gezeigt, wie in der ersten Hälfte des 19. Jahrhunderts der Grundstein für eine moderne Äquivalenzlexikographie gelegt wird und welchen Beitrag die Betrachtung der Autoren von Gebrauchswörterbüchern zur Ergänzung der italienischen Sprachgeschichte leisten kann.  aThis study presents the history of bilingual German-Italian lexicography prior to 1900. It provides a detailed analysis of the lexicographical and language didactic works of Francesco Valentini, a Roman scholar working in Berlin. Through his example, it shows how a foundation was created for a modern lexicography of equivalence in the first half of the 19th century.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aItalian philologyxStudy and teachingzGermanyzBerlin. 0aLexicographyxHistory. 4aFremdsprachenunterricht. 4aLexikographie. 4aZweisprachiges Wörterbuch. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aBilingual Dictionaries.  aForeign Language Teaching.  aHistory of German-Italian Lexicography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2016z9783110485257oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831104478280 cprintz978311044772940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311044989140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110449891423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110449891/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-076250-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1b2016  aEBA